title:
Russian Cyber Onslaught was Blunted by Ukrainian Cyber Resilience, not
  Merely Security
authors:
Alexander Kott, George (Yegor) Dubynskyi, Andrii Paziuk, Stephanie E.
  Galaitsi, Benjamin D. Trump, Igor Linkov
abstract:
Russian cyberattacks on Ukraine largely failed to produce meaningful outcomes
not merely due to robust Ukrainian cyber defenses but were instead primarily a
result of Ukraine's effective cyber resilience.
